
    1. Navigate to desired directory
        mkdir ~/my-ansible-project
        cd ~/my-ansible-project

    2. Create Virtual environment
        python3 -m venv ansible_env
        (creates a folder called ansible_env in ~/my-anisble-project)

    3. Activate virtual environment
        source ansible_env/bin/activate

    4. Install ansible in the virtual environment
        pip install ansible

    *** 5. Deactivate the virtual environment ***
        deactivate

    6. ??? Install the Docker Collection for the playbook
        ansible-galaxy collection install community.docker

    7. ??? Create your playbook (deploy.yml) and inventory (inventory.ini)
    in working directory.
        ~/my-ansible-project/
        └── ansible_env/  # Created by `python3 -m venv ansible_env`
            ├── bin/
            │   ├── activate
            │   ├── ansible  # Installed here after `pip install ansible`
            │   └── ...
            ├── lib/
            ├── deploy.yml
            └── inventory.ini

    8. ??? Run the playbook (while in the virtual)
        ansible-playbook -i inventory.ini deploy.yml